Sofacy.description:
Sofacy is a russian cyber espionage group which is associated with Main Intelligence Directorate of the General Staff of the Armed Forces of the Russian Federation.
This APT groups is known to target sensitive organizations and personnels world-wide including military, goverment and secrity organizations.
Sofacy is associated with many prominent attacks such as the attack on Hillary Clinton's campaign, the French television station TV5Monde, the White House, NATO, the Democratic National Committee, the Organization for Security and Co-operation in Europe and the campaign of French presidential candidate Emmanuel Macron.

Agent.BTZ.description:
A sophisticated worm that had the ability to spread through a network and flash drives, gather sensitive information and send data to a remote command and control server.
Agent.BTZ is known for its major role for the Cyberattack on the United States in 2008, which is also known as "worst breach of U.S. military computers in history".
Agent.BTZ.similarities: Agent.BTZ is known to be the ancestor of ComRAT, Carbon and Uroburos.

references.title: Agent.btz: a Source of Inspiration? - Kaspersky
Agent.btz - A Threat That Hit Pentagon - Threat Expert
The Uroburos case: new sophisticated RAT identified - G Data
New Variants of Agent.BTZ/ComRAT Found - Intezer

Carbon - Communication Library (v3.62).description:
The Carbon malware is an extensible framework which behaves as a plugin-manager for plugins that are provided by its Command and Control server.
The framework is advanced and comlciated and includes orchestrators, dropper, downloaders and a library to be injected to browsers and email clients.

references.title: Analysis of Project Cobra - G DATA

ComRAT.description: A Remote Access Tool and a direct descendant of the Agent.BTZ malware. More accurately, ComRAT is the name that was given to newer versions of Agent.BTZ after a big rfactoring that was done on the malware.
ComRAT.similarities: Naturally, ComRAT is sharing many similarities with its ancestor Agent.BTZ and with Uroburos and Carbon.

references.title: Evolution of sophisticated spyware: from Agent.BTZ to ComRAT - G DATA
New Variants of Agent.BTZ/ComRAT Found - Intezer

Kazuar.description:
Kazuar is a .NET written backdoor malware that gives to is operator the ability to gain a complete remote access to infected machines.
It is an extensible backdoor that has the ability to load additional plugins in order to increase its Trojan abilities.
Kazuar.similarities: Kazuar have chacteristic similarities to Gazer and Carbon.

references.title: Kazuar: Multiplatform Espionage Backdoor with API Access - Palo Alto

KSL0T - Keylogger.description: KSL0T is a Keylogger module that was inspected downloaded by Turla.

LightNeuron - Companion DLL.description: Light Neuron is a backdoor which designed to target Microsoft Exchange main servers. In addition of being a full-feature backdoor, its uniqueness is in its ability to spy on emails.

Outlook Backdoor.description: A backdoor that was inspected used by the Turla actor. It steals emails by forwarding all outgoing mails to the operators an also using email messages as a transport layer for its C&C protocol.

references.title: Turla Outlook Backdoor: Analysis of an unusual Turla backdoor

Penquin Turla.description:
Penquin Turla is a Linux version of the infamous Uroburos\Snake malware.
The malware contains ability to execute arbitrary commands sent to it from remote command and control servers.

references.title: The 'Penquin' Turla
Penquin's Moonlit Maze

PNG Dropper.description:
A second stage dropper that stored several PNG images in its resources while the actual payload was a PE binary that was splitted between the PNG. Upon executing, the dropper will combine the relevant parts from the stored PNG images into an executable PE that it will dynamically (reflectively) load to its memory.
The PNG dropper observed dropping Uroburos.

references.title: Carbon Black Threat Research Dissects PNG Dropper

Turla PNG Dropper is back
 - NCC Group

Uroburos.description:
Uroburos is a complex rootkit that was used by Turla. It is a successor of the infamous Agent.BTZ.
Uroburos composed of a driver and an encrypted VFS. It is able to take full control of infected systems, execute arbitrary commands and steal sensitive information.
Uroburos.similarities: Successor of Agent.BTZ. Share similarities with Agent.BTZ, ComRAT and Carbon.

references.title: Uroburos - highly complex espionage software with Russian roots - G Data
Uroburos – Deeper travel into kernel protection mitigation - G Data
The Epic Turla Operation - Kaspersky

Wipbot.description: Wipbot is a downloader trojan with limited backdoor functionality. It can execute arbitrary commands and download additional malicious components to the machine.

references.title: The Waterbug attack group - Symantec
The Epic Turla Operation - Kaspersky

Cannon.description: Cannon is a Trojan with variants written in C# and Delphi. It was first observed in April 2018. The Trojan is usually being used as a secong-stage payload which is downloaded by one of Zebrocy's variants.

references.title: Sofacy Continues Global Attacks and Wheels Out New 'Cannon' Trojan - Palo Alto
